 ENDF/B-VII   January 2006, G.Hale, P.G.Young (LANL)               425 1451
                                                                   425 1451
 A simplified revision of the 9Be file has been made for the       425 1451
 first release of ENDF/B-VII based on a single-channel R-matrix    425 1451
 analysis of the n+9Be total cross section.  This analysis fits    425 1451
 the total cross section data of refs [1-5] quite well at          425 1451
 energies up to 5 MeV.  However, since it is single-channel,       425 1451
 the analysis does not give the partitioning of the total cross    425 1451
 section into its constituent parts [(n,n), (n,2n),...] above      425 1451
 the lowest (n,2n) threshold.  Therefore, the reaction cross       425 1451
 sections were unchanged, and the elastic cross section (MT=2)     425 1451
 was obtained by subtracting the total nonelastic cross section    425 1451
 from the revised total cross section at energies below 5 MeV.     425 1451
 Nothing above that energy was changed.  The elastic scattering    425 1451
 angular distributions (MF=4,MT=2) were also kept the same at      425 1451
 all energies.                                                     425 1451
                                                                   425 1451
 The reason for this simple modification is that integral          425 1451
 experiments with Be reflectors indicated that the elastic         425 1451
 cross section should be reduced at low energies.  The new         425 1451
 fit to the total cross section gave this behavior, especially     425 1451
 at energies in the minimum before the first resonance at          425 1451
 625 keV.  Preliminary testing has verified that these changes     425 1451
 improve the performance of the 9Be cross sections in reflected    425 1451
 integral experiments somewhat, but that additional future         425 1451
 improvements would be desirable.                                  425 1451
